ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project

Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

Notes: e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version
0 = Does NOT meet DSM-5 criteria; 1 = Meets full criteria for DSM-5

ElementDescription: "DISC (Parent): Separation anxiety disorder past month (0=Negative; 1=Positive, DSM IV Code 309.21)"
Notes: 0 = Negative; 1 = Positive, DSM IV Code 309.21; NA = Not available

ElementDescription: Conduct disorder/antisocial personality disorder. past month: diagnosis for conduct disorder
AD9: Bipolar I (current/ recentepisode)Note: TADS and SOFTAD visits.TADS diagnosis of current or SOFTAD diagnosis of recent defined as met criterion when condition at its worse since last visit.
"Screening and Exclusion Form (0:0 to 4:5 y:m) Question VF10 Child of Interest (COI) diagnosed with Reactive Attachment Disorder (Y=Yes, N=No, NA=Not Available)"
Notes: Y = Yes; N = No; NA = Not available

ElementDescription: Oppositional Defiant Disorder - Fits consensus diagnosis any time in life
